race.description: Apg - Vicbred Super Series Final Mobile Pace (G2)
race.comment: Looks a battle of the Emma Stewart stablemates but the ace draw gives WAR DAN BUDDY (1) every chance to come out on top. He was impressive when he went straight to the front and cruised home by nearly 14m in last week's semi final. Should find that spot again and if allowed to dictate will be hard to get past. MIKI TO SUCCESS (9) draws on the back line again but is in terrific form having won his last four starts, three of them from this row. Has only once been beaten in his last seven and that was from a tough draw in The Eureka. Won the 3CG edition of this last year and doesn't lack for class. DEE ROE (4) showed good improvement for second to Miki Success from the back row in the semis. Should be close to his peak third-up and from a better draw is a trifecta hope. OUR ROCKER (11) and SIR JIMMY (6) are also from the Stewart camp and each has enough ability to fill a place in the exotics with even luck.
